Preconditions:
The input integers `h` and `w` must be positive.
The arrays `horizontalCuts` and `verticalCuts` must not be null.
The arrays `horizontalCuts` and `verticalCuts` must contain only positive integers.
The elements in the arrays `horizontalCuts` and `verticalCuts` must be less than or equal to `h` and `w` respectively.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value.
The returned value should be the maximum area of a piece of cake after cutting at each horizontal and vertical position provided in the arrays `horizontalCuts` and `verticalCuts`.
The returned value should be modulo `10^9 + 7`.